    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Early type of percussion lock using a metal tube inserted into a hole in the breech to contain the priming powder, instead of the percussion cap which became standard later.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
